{
  "texts": [
    "We observed that using the first 1,500 tokens yielded better results in most cases than using the first 3,000 tokens in the GPT-3.5Turbo model.",
    "This is likely because the essential information for diagnosis, such as patient medical history, is generally found at the beginning of the note, while the latter part often contains irrelevant information like medication history.",
    "This suggests that segmenting relevant sections of the notes or using the summarized text from the models like BART could not only reduce costs but also enhance performance.",
    "Additionally, we found that removing a significant number of tokens or keywords related to metastatic cancer did not adversely affect performance.",
    "This finding is particularly important given that our input text is often incomplete."
  ]
}